data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer takes an expression tree

EF Core 10 changed the parameter from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your expression-tree building code **won't compile**. The fix is much simpler — use a regular lambda with imperative logic:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` / `Expression.Parameter` machinery.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two sub-changes

**a) Column uniquification.** If `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` both have a `Street` property, EF 10 auto-appends a number to disambiguate (e.g. `Street`, `Street1`). Previously they silently shared one column (data corruption risk). To keep explicit control, pin the names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** Your `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`; it now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

⚠️ **Both changes affect migrations** — if you have an existing database, EF will generate column renames. Pin names with `HasColumnName` to avoid unnecessary schema churn.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on this interface now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual executed SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
